  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were obviously-- I've never been in a DP camp, but there obviously must have been quite a lot of hospital work going on there as well because many of these people who survived concentration camps were obviously in a very, very poor state, to say the least.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Conversations were always difficult.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I found that in Israel later on as well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Although I spoke English and, and German and, and, and some school O-level French, which I, I found very useful on that, on that occasion there in France and Belgium.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "No, we spoke very little.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Most of those people spoke Yiddish or spoke Russian or spoke Polish or-- most of them were survivors of Eastern European Jewry.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For me it came to an end in so far that I was being relieved of the thing, and I was then sent onto a specific training course early on in the Alps where the intention was to have groups from different countries, no more than 10, to be trained in small arms combat so that when we went back to our respective countries, we could then train people here to go out to Palestine, as it then still was, and become active as fighters.",
      "word_count": 85
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Such things as how to kill somebody with a knife effectively, how to defend yourself against stick fighting, how to kill people with pistols, how to kill people in unarmed combat.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Arms, as such-- rifles, machine guns and so on-- were, of course, taboo, were not allowed in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so one had to use other means of-- of-- of-- of warfare as well.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't have rifles or bayonets, but we certainly had knives.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
